# C++ Executor Overlay

## Role
Apply this overlay when implementing C++ changes. Keep edits minimal, compile-safe, and scoped to requested behavior.

## Execution Rules
- Prefer smallest correct change over broad refactors.
- Preserve ABI/public interfaces unless explicitly requested.
- Avoid introducing heavy template metaprogramming unless required.
- Keep ownership/lifetime semantics explicit and safe.

## Validation Expectations
- Build changed targets (or nearest module) before completion.
- Run relevant tests for touched components.
- Surface compiler warnings that indicate potential correctness risk.

## Typical Verification Commands
- `cmake --build <build-dir> --target <target>`
- `ctest --test-dir <build-dir> --output-on-failure`
- `clang-tidy <file>` (if configured)

## Output Requirement
Report:
- changed files
- build/test commands executed
- result status and any residual risks
